<font color="#FF0000">HUMBLE HAYSEED-HICK</font><br>
<tt>Fri Aug  8 19:58:46 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Doctor Barry Spatz:<br><br>
I am leaving the parking lot, in a sense. I am guilty of throwing out the baby with the bathwater.<br>
While I oppose your views and most of your values, I do not have the right to force mine upon you.  I do not have the right to attack you as a person.  I advocate that no man can tell another man what to do.  You and I, both, have the right to do whatever we want to do and either enjoy or suffer the consequences.<br>
Because of my service in Viet Nam I was cursed and abused... I was nine hours late in returning home from my first tour of duty because a taxi cab driver refused to let me in his cab while I was in uniform. I have been ridiculed and mocked.  <br>
Conversely, I was decorated seventy-six times for Gallantry, Heroism, Meritorious Service and for five gunshot wounds and a broken back.  Twenty two thousand people stood and applauded me for seventeen minutes.  On June the 27th, 1990 I was honored by the Second Session of the 101st Congress of the United States of America.  I have had the bitter and the sweet.<br>
Above all this, I continue to suffer for having killed quite a few Vietnamese children.  I lost many very good friends.  On one occassion, my co-pilot was shot in the head.  I was flying.  It took what seemed like a thousand years to ascend above the tree tops, before I could wipe away some of his gray matter which dangled from the tip of my nose.<br>
I don't remember the hundreds of men whose lives I saved by evacuating them under fire... I only focus upon the ones who did not make it.<br>
The intensity of my emotions sometimes overwhelms my cognitive resources.  I feel that the same may have happened to you (I will not put words into your mouth.)<br>
I believe that you want acceptance from myself and other veterans.  I, too, would welcome acceptance from those who rejected me thirty-one years ago and continue to do so today.<br>
It is possible that I may hate war more that you.  Dwell on that for a moment.  But, I do not have to hate you.<br>
I do not wish to assail your values, but I will pray to God in my own manner that He will impart wisdom to both of us.<br><br>
In the meantime, I wish you good health and good fortune.<br><br>
Captain Edward Ramon<br>
RVN 1966-67-69<br>
U.S. Army Fifth Special Forces A-235, A-412, B-31, B-32<br>
U.S. Navy Special Operations (Seawolf) Seal Team 2
